JD - 7 :

Accountabilities:

AI Application Development & Configuration:
• Develop and configure AI applications within the Moveworks platform to address specific business use cases and employee experience challenges.
• Build and maintain chatbot conversations, workflows, and automated responses using Moveworks Creator Studio and configuration tools.
• Implement ServiceNow NowAssist capabilities and integrate AI-powered features within ITSM processes.
• Configure Microsoft Copilot integrations and customize AI assistants for enterprise use cases.

Integration & Automation:
• Design and implement API integrations between Moveworks, ServiceNow, and other enterprise systems using MuleSoft and other integration platforms.
• Develop automated workflows using n8n, Make, and other workflow automation tools.
• Create and maintain data pipelines for knowledge ingestion and AI model training.
• Implement RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) solutions for enterprise knowledge management.

Technical Implementation & Support:
• Configure and maintain AI models, including fine-tuning and optimization for enterprise use cases.
• Implement A2A (Application-to-Application) integrations and MCP solutions.
• Develop custom connectors and extensions for AI platform capabilities.
• Support incident resolution and troubleshooting of AI application issues.

Quality Assurance & Testing:
• Conduct thorough testing of AI applications, including conversation flows, integrations, and automated processes.
• Implement monitoring and alerting for AI application performance and accuracy.
• Ensure AI solutions meet security, compliance, and data governance requirements.
• Perform regular maintenance and updates of AI applications and integrations.

Collaboration & Documentation:
• Work closely with business analysts and collaborators to understand requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
• Collaborate with the Platform Systems Administrator on release management and change control processes.
• Create and maintain technical documentation for AI applications, integrations, and workflows.
• Provide technical guidance and support to end-users and business teams.

Essential Skills/Experience:
• Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or related field, or equivalent experience.
• 3+ years of experience in AI application development, enterprise software development, or related technical role.
• Demonstrable experience in implementing AI solutions in enterprise environments.
• Hands-on experience with Generative AI platforms, Large Language Models (LLMs), and AI application development.
• Experience with Microsoft Copilot configuration, customization, and enterprise deployment.
• Knowledge of ServiceNow NowAssist implementation and AI-powered ITSM capabilities.
• Understanding of RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation), LangChain, and other AI frameworks.
• Experience with Agentic AI concepts and implementation.
• Proficiency in API development and integration technologies.
• Experience with workflow automation tools (n8n, Make, or similar platforms).
• Proficiency in enterprise integration patterns and standard processes.
• Understanding of data governance, security, and compliance requirements for AI applications.
• Experience with version control systems and DevOps practices.
• Experience with Moveworks platform configuration and development.
• ServiceNow platform knowledge, including workflow development and system administration.
• Understanding of ITSM processes and ITIL framework.
• Experience with Microsoft 365 ecosystem and enterprise applications.
• Strong problem-solving and analytical thinking abilities.
• Excellent communication skills with ability to explain technical concepts to non-technical collaborators.
• Ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.
• Collaborative approach with experience working in multi-functional teams.

Desirable Skills/Experience:
• Experience with MuleSoft Anypoint Platform for enterprise integrations.
• Knowledge of pharmaceutical industry regulations and compliance requirements (HIPAA, GDPR, GxP).
• Advanced certifications in AI/ML platforms or enterprise software development.
• Experience with cloud platforms (Azure, AWS) and containerization technologies.
• Understanding of AI/ML governance, ethics, and responsible AI practices.
• Experience with deep learning frameworks and model optimization techniques.
• Understanding natural language processing (NLP) and conversational AI guidelines.
• Familiarity with enterprise knowledge management systems and content ingestion processes.
• Relevant certifications in Moveworks, ServiceNow, or Microsoft platforms.
• ITIL Foundation certification or higher.
• Agile/Scrum methodology experience and certifications.
• Experience in Lean and Agile ways of working.
• Experience in pharmaceutical, healthcare, or highly regulated industries.
• Understanding of employee experience design and user-centered development approaches.
• Project management experience with technical implementation projects.
• Experience with change management and user adoption strategies.

